From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matthew Feickert <matthew.feickert@cern.ch>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 17:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: Do not put side effects inside assert()

The LoopTools integral cache (src/LT/cache.c) and the external
self-energy helper (src/Util/extself.c) place calls with required side
effects -- malloc(), mkdtemp(), pipe(), fork() -- *inside* assert().

When the C preprocessor macro NDEBUG is defined (which conda-forge does
by default via CPPFLAGS for release builds), assert(expr) expands to a
no-op and `expr` is never evaluated. The malloc() in cache.c is then
never called, leaving `node` NULL, and the immediately following
`node->succ = NULL;` dereferences a NULL pointer -> SIGSEGV at runtime
(e.g. during FHHiggsCorr loop-integral evaluation).

This is why FeynHiggs built with distribution toolchains (which do not
define NDEBUG) runs fine, while a conda-forge build segfaults despite an
otherwise identical configuration.

Move the side-effecting calls out of assert() so they always execute;
assert() is kept purely as a success check. Verified to produce
bit-identical Higgs masses to a build with assert active.
---
 src/LT/cache.c       | 3 ++-
 src/Util/extself.c   | 9 ++++++---
 2 files changed, 8 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

--- a/src/LT/cache.c
+++ b/src/LT/cache.c
@@ -129,7 +129,8 @@
 	   an integer index into base */
     size_t mem = sizeof(Node) +
       npara*sizeof(RealType) + nval*sizeof(ComplexType);
-    assert( (node = malloc(mem)) );
+    node = malloc(mem);
+    assert( node );
     node = (Node *)((char *)node +
       (PtrDiff(base, &node->para[npara]) & (sizeof(ComplexType) - 1)));
     node->succ = NULL;
--- a/src/Util/extself.c
+++ b/src/Util/extself.c
@@ -114,9 +114,12 @@
     strcat(tmpdir_template, "/fh-extse.XXXXXX");
   }
   strcpy(tmpdir, tmpdir_template);
-  assert( mkdtemp(tmpdir) != NULL &&
-          pipe(fd) != -1 &&
-          (pid = fork()) != -1 );
+  char *tmpdir_ok = mkdtemp(tmpdir);
+  int pipe_ok = pipe(fd);
+  pid = fork();
+  assert( tmpdir_ok != NULL &&
+          pipe_ok != -1 &&
+          pid != -1 );
 
   if( pid == 0 ) {
     close(0);
